          "id": "caae2a805411fc40a7b3f5fa6276e62754f99a88",
          "message": "feat(cli): add `katana bootstrap` subcommand  (#528)\n\n## Summary\n\nAdds a new `katana bootstrap` subcommand for declaring classes and\ndeploying contracts on a running katana node, with both a programmatic\nCLI and a full ratatui TUI. Lives in a new top-level `crates/bootstrap`\nworkspace crate; `bin/katana` only mounts the clap entry point.\n\n## What's in it\n\n- **Programmatic mode** — TOML manifest (`--manifest`), repeatable\n`--declare` / `--deploy` flags, embedded class registry (currently\n`dev_account`, registry abstraction in place for\nOZ/Controller/ERC20/ERC721 follow-ups). Idempotent by default:\nalready-declared classes and already-deployed contracts are silently\nskipped via `is_declared` / `is_deployed` prechecks; skipped ops don't\nburn a nonce.\n- **Interactive TUI** — multi-tab app (Classes / Contracts / Settings /\nExecute) with: fuzzy `*.json` file picker (cwd walk, debounced, ignores\ncommon heavy dirs), background Sierra→CASM compile on a worker thread\nwith a dedicated centred loader modal, dedup with yellow `*` markers +\ninline \"Class is already selected\" notices, readline-style text editing\n(Ctrl+A/E/B/F/W/U/K), live-streaming Execute tab with per-row spinner /\n✓ / ✗ states.\n- **Executor** — starknet-rs `SingleOwnerAccount` for declare_v3 /\ndeploy_v3, `katana_utils::TxWaiter` for tx confirmation. Explicit nonce\nthreading so multiple txs from the same account batch correctly.\nStreaming `BootstrapEvent` channel for the TUI's progress view.\n- **Tests** — 40 unit + integration tests in the new crate, including a\njsonrpsee-based mock RPC server that records every incoming method call\nso the integration tests can assert on tx type / count / nonces.\n\n---------\n\nCo-authored-by: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
